#. <section class="sutta" id="an4.29"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.29:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.29:0.2"
msgid "3. Uruvelavagga"
msgstr "3. At Uruvelā"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.29:0.3"
msgid "29. Dhammapadasutta"
msgstr "29. Basic Principles"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an4.29:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, dhammapadāni aggaññāni rattaññāni vaṃsaññāni "
"porāṇāni asaṅkiṇṇāni asaṅkiṇṇapubbāni, na saṅkīyanti na saṅkīyissanti, "
"appaṭikuṭṭhāni samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhi."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, these four basic principles are original, long-standing, "
"traditional, and ancient. They are uncorrupted, as they have been since the "
"beginning. They’re not being corrupted now nor will they be. Sensible "
"ascetics and brahmins don’t look down on them."

msgctxt "an4.29:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni cattāri?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "an4.29:1.3"
msgid ""
"Anabhijjhā, bhikkhave, dhammapadaṃ aggaññaṃ rattaññaṃ vaṃsaññaṃ porāṇaṃ "
"asaṅkiṇṇaṃ asaṅkiṇṇapubbaṃ, na saṅkīyati na saṅkīyissati, appaṭikuṭṭhaṃ "
"samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhi."
msgstr "Contentment, good will, right mindfulness, and right immersion."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an4.29:2.1"
msgid ""
"Abyāpādo, bhikkhave, dhammapadaṃ aggaññaṃ rattaññaṃ vaṃsaññaṃ porāṇaṃ "
"asaṅkiṇṇaṃ asaṅkiṇṇapubbaṃ, na saṅkīyati na saṅkīyissati, appaṭikuṭṭhaṃ "
"samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhi."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an4.29:3.1"
msgid ""
"Sammāsati, bhikkhave, dhammapadaṃ aggaññaṃ rattaññaṃ vaṃsaññaṃ porāṇaṃ "
"asaṅkiṇṇaṃ asaṅkiṇṇapubbaṃ, na saṅkīyati na saṅkīyissati, appaṭikuṭṭhaṃ "
"samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhi."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an4.29:4.1"
msgid ""
"Sammāsamādhi, bhikkhave, dhammapadaṃ aggaññaṃ rattaññaṃ vaṃsaññaṃ porāṇaṃ "
"asaṅkiṇṇaṃ asaṅkiṇṇapubbaṃ, na saṅkīyati na saṅkīyissati, appaṭikuṭṭhaṃ "
"samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an4.29:4.2"
msgid ""
"Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri dhammapadāni aggaññāni rattaññāni vaṃsaññāni "
"porāṇāni asaṅkiṇṇāni asaṅkiṇṇapubbāni, na saṅkīyanti na saṅkīyissanti, "
"appaṭikuṭṭhāni samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhīti."
msgstr ""
"These four basic principles are original, long-standing, traditional, and "
"ancient. They are uncorrupted, as they have been since the beginning. They’"
"re not being corrupted now nor will they be. Sensible ascetics and brahmins "
"don’t look down on them."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an4.29:5.1"
msgid "Anabhijjhālu vihareyya,"
msgstr "You should live with contentment,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.29:5.2"
msgid "abyāpannena cetasā;"
msgstr "and a heart of good will,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: ekaggacittassa → ekaggacittāyaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an4.29:5.3"
msgid "Sato ekaggacittassa,"
msgstr "mindful, with unified mind,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.29:5.4"
msgid "ajjhattaṃ susamāhito”ti."
msgstr "serene within.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.29:5.5"
msgid "Navamaṃ."
msgstr ""
